FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
INTERNSHIP LOGGING AND EVALUATION SYSTEM (ILES) will able to do the following
- manage users (STudents and Supervisors) or Roles
- provide internship Placement (Internship placement module)
- Allow weekly logs by students for work done and later on report evaluation by supervisiors (weekly log book module)
- Allow work supervisors to review work flow
- Weighted score computation
- Academic evaluation by Academic supervisors
- Dashboards and reporting

NON FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
The ILES system will be a web based platform composed of a website having the following
HTML- HYPER TEXT MARKUP LANGUAGE (HTML)-responsible for the structure of the webpage
CSS-Cascading Style Sheets - For styling the HTML webpage like adding graphics, colur excetra
JAVASCRIPT- For determining the behaviour of the webpage and website.
This system has two parts namely:
THE FRONT END - Enables users to browse to the website and make a request. developed by software professionals known as front End  using JAVASCRIPT
THE BACK END - Its the server end and holds the information or requests needed or requested for those browsing and responds to them "a term we call RESPONSE."
The BACKEND is developed using DJANGO

